title: ESA troubleshooting JUICE radar antenna
summary: A radar antenna on a European mission to Jupiter has yet to fully deploy after launch, although project officials say they still have plenty of options to fix the problem.

title: SpaceX Falcon Heavy launches first ViaSat-3 satellite
summary: SpaceX launched the Americas-focused ViaSat-3 broadband satellite on a Falcon Heavy rocket April 30 following delays partly caused by severe weather that included lightning and tornado warnings.

title: ViaSat-3 Americas launches on expendable Falcon Heavy
summary: Falcon Heavy’s second launch 2023 will try again on Sunday, with liftoff with the ViaSat-3 Americas satellite as the main payload, plus the much smaller Arcturus and G-Space 1 rideshare satellites.
